<TITLE> Shitalakhya river clean-up drive on </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Naryanganj, Oct 20 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Authority and Naryanganj district administration in a joint drive on Sunday dismantled illegal installations in surrounding areas of Kachpur Bridge on the Shitalakhya River. Demolition of shops, stone piles, sand banks, illegal installations ran from 11am to 3pm. Locals and officials said influential people has been illegally filling the river and carrying out sand and stone business for a long time. BIWTA targeted 60 such entities in the clean-up drive. Mahbubur Rahman, port and transport director of BIWTA, chief civil engineer Sadekul Islam, Naryanganj's first class magistrates Abdul Hye and Samshujjoha, BIWTA Naryanganj port's senior deputy director Abu Jafar Howlader and deputy director Alamgir Kabir oversaw the drive. Nearly 100 workers, BIWTA vessel 'Agrajatra' and workboats were used in the operation. Magistrate Hye said, "River boundaries have been demarcated with red flags. Owners have been given two days to move sand banks and stone piles. Or else, steps will be taken against the perpetrators." Large amounts of sand and stones were stacked up within river area. Deputy director Kabir said, "Sixty institutions were given licence to do business on the river banks. But the licenses have been cancelled on breach of conditions." bdn
